      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Andreas Dilger\n> 8:48 AM\n> Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1\n> So I see that this is removing the compatibilty code, which is good, but how does it ensure that the client has completed the connection to the other MDTs that was done in http://review.whamcloud.com/10958 ?\n\nAfter removing the redundant ibits compatibility check, the ldlm_enqueue request will not access non-initiaized export, and when the RPC is given to lower layer, the ptlrpc will handle the connection issues (connect/reconnect/replay/recovery) automatically.",
